{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# **Use case: Optimization**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## We are going to implement QAOA for the MaxCut problem\n",
    "\n",
    "we start by importing qiskit to simulate circuits and some other basic libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pylab as pl\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "networkx can be used to handle graphs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(array([0, 1]), array([0, 1]))"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "V = np.arange(0,2,1)\n",
    "E =[(0,1,1.0)] \n",
    "\n",
    "G = nx.Graph()\n",
    "G.add_nodes_from(V)\n",
    "G.add_weighted_edges_from(E)\n",
    "\n",
    "nx.draw_networkx(G)\n",
    "np.array(list(G.nodes)), V"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We define a function that creates our circuit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def createCircuit(x,G,depth):\n",
    "    V = list(G.nodes)\n",
    "    num_V = len(V)\n",
    "    q = QuantumRegister(num_V)\n",
    "    c = ClassicalRegister(num_V)\n",
    "    circ = QuantumCircuit(q,c)\n",
    "    #uniform superposition\n",
    "    circ.h(range(num_V))\n",
    "    circ.barrier()\n",
    "    for d in range(depth):\n",
    "        gamma=x[2*d]\n",
    "        beta=x[2*d+1]\n",
    "        #go through all edges and add Rzz gate\n",
    "        for edge in G.edges():\n",
    "            i=int(edge[0])\n",
    "            j=int(edge[1])\n",
    "            w = G[i][j]['weight']\n",
    "            circ.cx(q[i],q[j])\n",
    "            circ.rz(w*gamma,q[j])\n",
    "            circ.cx(q[i],q[j])\n",
    "        circ.barrier()\n",
    "        #add the mixer\n",
    "        circ.rx(2*beta,range(num_V))\n",
    "        circ.barrier()\n",
    "    circ.measure(q,c)\n",
    "    return circ"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "draw example circuits"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 701.433x204.68 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "createCircuit(np.array((np.pi,np.pi)),G,1).draw(output='mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1062.78x204.68 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "createCircuit(np.array((np.pi,np.pi,1,2)),G,2).draw(output='mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "in order to evaluate a solution we define a function that gives us the cost"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cost(x,G):\n",
    "    C=0\n",
    "    for edge in G.edges():\n",
    "        i = int(edge[0])\n",
    "        j = int(edge[1])\n",
    "        w = G[i][j]['weight']\n",
    "        C = C + w/2*(1-(2*x[i]-1)*(2*x[j]-1))\n",
    "    return C"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "brute force function that lists all 2^n possibilities and finds the best solutions (use with caution)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def listcosts(G):\n",
    "    costs={}\n",
    "    maximum=0\n",
    "    solutions=[]\n",
    "    V = list(G.nodes)\n",
    "    num_V = len(V)\n",
    "    for i in range(2**num_V):\n",
    "        binstring=\"{0:b}\".format(i).zfill(num_V)\n",
    "        y=[int(i) for i in binstring]\n",
    "        costs[binstring]=cost(y,G)\n",
    "        maximum = max(maximum,costs[binstring])\n",
    "    for key in costs:\n",
    "        if costs[key]==maximum:\n",
    "            solutions.append(key)\n",
    "    return costs, maximum, solutions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "({'00': 0.0, '01': 1.0, '10': 1.0, '11': 0.0}, 1.0, ['01', '10'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "listcosts(G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "the result of a circuit contains a dictionary containing bitstrings together with how many times they have occured\n",
    "\n",
    "we define a function that gives us (an approximation of) the expectationvalue based on this"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def expectationValue(data,G):\n",
    "    res=data.result().results\n",
    "    E=[]\n",
    "    V = list(G.nodes)\n",
    "    num_V = G.number_of_nodes()\n",
    "    for result in res:\n",
    "        n_shots = result.shots\n",
    "        counts = result.data.counts\n",
    "        e = 0\n",
    "        for hexkey in list(counts.keys()):\n",
    "            count = counts[hexkey]\n",
    "            binstring = \"{0:b}\".format(int(hexkey,0)).zfill(num_V)\n",
    "            y=[int(i) for i in binstring]\n",
    "            e += cost(y,G)*count/n_shots\n",
    "        E.append(-e)\n",
    "    return E"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "we will use an ideal simulator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ideal_sim = Aer.get_backend('qasm_simulator')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "to get the energy/training/cost landscape for depth p=1, we sample the region $[0,\\frac{\\pi}{2}]^2$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "circuits=[]\n",
    "n=16\n",
    "for gamma in np.linspace(0,np.pi,n):\n",
    "    for beta in np.linspace(0,np.pi,n):\n",
    "        circuits.append(createCircuit(np.array((gamma,beta)),G,1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "job_sim = execute(circuits, ideal_sim, shots=1024*2*2*2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "val=expectationValue(job_sim,G)\n",
    "E=np.array(val).reshape(n,n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 480x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f = pl.figure(figsize=(6, 6), dpi= 80, facecolor='w', edgecolor='k');\n",
    "_=pl.xlabel(r'$\\gamma$')\n",
    "_=pl.ylabel(r'$\\beta$')\n",
    "ax = pl.gca()\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(E,interpolation='bicubic',origin='lower',extent=[0,np.pi,0,np.pi])\n",
    "divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)\n",
    "cax = divider.append_axes(\"right\", size=\"5%\", pad=0.05)\n",
    "_=pl.colorbar(im, cax=cax)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "we import minimizers from scipy to do local minimization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import optimize as opt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "the minimize funciton needs a function to evalution, which we create next"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def getval(x, backend):\n",
    "    circ=createCircuit(x,G,1)\n",
    "    tcirc = transpile(circ, backend)\n",
    "    j = execute(tcirc, backend, shots=1024*2*2*2)\n",
    "    val=expectationValue(j,G)\n",
    "    return val[0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Optimization terminated successfully.\n",
      "         Current function value: -1.000000\n",
      "         Iterations: 18\n",
      "         Function evaluations: 36\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "out=opt.minimize(getval, x0=(1, 1), method='Nelder-Mead',\\\n",
    "                 args=(ideal_sim),\\\n",
    "             options={'xatol': 1e-2, 'fatol': 1e-2, 'disp': True})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 480x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f = pl.figure(figsize=(6, 6), dpi= 80, facecolor='w', edgecolor='k');\n",
    "_=pl.xlabel(r'$\\beta$')\n",
    "_=pl.ylabel(r'$\\gamma$')\n",
    "ax = pl.gca()\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(E,interpolation='bicubic',origin='lower',extent=[0,np.pi,0,np.pi])\n",
    "_=pl.plot(out.x[1],out.x[0],'xr')\n",
    "divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)\n",
    "cax = divider.append_axes(\"right\", size=\"5%\", pad=0.05)\n",
    "_=pl.colorbar(im, cax=cax)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "let's plot the histogram"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "metadata": {},

    "noisy_circuits=[]\n",
